**Proof**
If $A = ğ± ğ²^âŠ¤$ then all columns are multiples of $ğ±$, that is the column span has dimension 1. 
On the other hand, if $A$ has rank-1 then its columns span
a one-dimensional subspace: there exists $ğ± âˆˆ ğ”½^m$
