## Lab and Problem Sheet

In the problem sheet we see some pen-and-paper examples of LU and PLU factorisations, to emphasise the relationship
with Gaussian elimination with or without pivoting. In the lab we focus on the practical usage of LU and PLU factorisations
using the inbuilt commands, observing that the PLU factorisation is what is used in practice.  We also investigate a special  ``bad matrix" where PLU factorisation surprisingly fails. This might raise the question why we use PLU factorisation despite the chance of faiulure, but as we  see in he lab the probability of encountering such
a matrix is extremely small. The biggest open problem in numerical linear algebra is proving this observation rigorously.